$ /etc/R/Renviron

The purpose of the Renviron file is to set → development/environment-variable[environment variables].

It might contain something like
code {
LC_COLLATE  = "English_United States.1252"
LC_CTYPE    = "English_United States.1252"
LC_MONETARY = "English_United States.1252"
LC_NUMERIC  = "English_United States.1252"
LC_TIME     = "English_United States.1252"
code }

In an R session, it can be edited or created using → development/languages/R/functions/file/edit[`file.edit()`]:
code {
renv = path.expand(file.path('~', '.Renviron'));
file.edit(renv);
code }

sa:
  → development/languages/R/files
